*σάββατον / sabbaton / sab'-bat-on
=== Etymology ===

*Of Hebrew origin [{{HH|7676}}]; the Sabbath (that is, Shabbath), or day of weekly repose from secular avocations (also the observance or institution itself); by extension a se'nnight, that is, the interval between two Sabbaths; likewise the plural in all the above applications: 
=== Noun ===
[[sabbath]] (day), [[week]].